1993.assessment:
Public debt approximately 110% of GDP in 1993. Fourth Republic begun;
fiscal challenges inherited. Post-election spending adding to debt.
HIPC eligibility assessment not yet reached.

1992.assessment:
Ghana's GDP per capita approximately $419 in 1992 (16.8% of 2024 peak).
Democratic transition year; economy stable. Rawlings won elections;
economic reform program continuing under Fourth Republic.

1993.assessment:
Trade approximately 52% of GDP in 1993. Fourth Republic inaugurated;
trade policy continuity. Moderate trade openness with commodity exports
dominant. Ghana ECOWAS integration supporting regional trade.

2003.assessment:
Formal unemployment approximately 5% in 2003. Economy growing;
employment broadly stable. HIPC completion point reached.
Ghana achieving middle-income trajectory aspirations.

2010.assessment:
Formal unemployment approximately 5.8% in 2010. Oil production begun;
economy booming. Employment growth supported by strong GDP growth.
Major GDP rebasing did not directly affect employment statistics.

1998.assessment:
Full diplomatic integration in 1998. Ghana approaching HIPC threshold;
international financial institutions engagement strong. Active in
Commonwealth, UN, ECOWAS, OAU. Strong bilateral relations.

1992.assessment:
Minimal displacement from Ghana in 1992. Democratic transition year;
no political violence causing flight. Ghana hosting West African
refugees. Net inflows (receiving) rather than outflows.

1996.assessment:
Minimal displacement from Ghana in 1996. Election year; peaceful
process with no political violence causing flight. Ghana stable;
hosting West African refugees.

2000.assessment:
Minimal displacement from Ghana in 2000. First peaceful power transfer;
no political violence. Economic difficulties not severe enough to
cause mass emigration as refugees. Ghana receiving African refugees.

2007.assessment:
Minimal displacement from Ghana. 50th independence celebrations;
stability and national pride high. Ghana hosting Liberian and Ivorian
refugees. No Ghanaian refugee flows.

2016.assessment:
Minimal displacement from Ghana. Third peaceful power transfer;
no political displacement. Ghana stable. Economic emigration (not
refugee) exists but formal refugee flows negligible.

2024.assessment:
Minimal displacement from Ghana. Fourth peaceful power transfer;
no political displacement. Ghana economic recovery underway.
Ghana continues hosting West African and Sahelian refugees.

Minimal violence in 2024 election year. Elections peaceful. Mahama won;
Akufo-Addo conceded. No political violence. Ghana maintained its
exemplary peaceful democracy record.

2016.assessment:
No OBS in 2016. Estimated around 49-52. Third peaceful power transfer;
budget transparency maintained through transition. IMF program providing
fiscal accountability framework.
